LAGOS – United Breeds Foundation, a harm reduction organisation is set to begin a major traffic control service that will benefit motorists who drive through Apple junction, Amuwo Odofin area of Lagos state. A statement co-signed by the convener, David Ohiembor and the Youth coordinator of the project, Micheal Onuwaje Teinro explained that gridlock in the area has become recalcitrant, adding that it was necessary to come up with an initiative that would help manage the situation. The statement, therefore, reads: “We are informing residents and the road users to cooperate with this development. Also, thank the police division Festac and the Area E Command for their efforts in training our youths. In partnership, we shall work out a better Amuwo”. -Advertisement- Ohiembor in the statement also appealed to individuals and corporate bodies, to support the initiative which would commence on the 18th of May, 20222, adding, ‘’individuals and corporate bodies who would like to support us in cash and kind are welcomed. As it will be cost-effective to engage these youths through this period’’.